# Project-wide Normalization: 'landing' vs 'page'

## Goal
Ensure 'landing' is only used for the / route (site homepage) and not for generic page/section/item logic. Normalize all generic usage to 'page'.

## Steps
1. Audit all comments, utility functions, and grengo CLI/tooling for use of the term 'landing'.
2. Update comments, function names, and documentation to use 'page' instead of 'landing' for generic usage.
3. Rename the LandingSkeleton component and its file to PageSkeleton (or similar), and update all imports/usages to match.
4. Update any references to LandingSkeleton in the frontend (e.g., PageBuilder, error/loading states) to use the new 'page' terminology.
5. Review all grengo commands, help text, and code for 'landing' usage and update to 'page' where appropriate.
6. Add a test/validation step to ensure no generic usage of 'landing' remains outside of the / route context.
